<font color="#FF0000">ATTITUDES TOWARD ME?</font><br>
<tt>Fri Apr 18  6:19:36 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I am a 22 year-old Vietnamese refugee/US citizen in graduate school, doing work on Vietnamese re-membering practices about the war. I'm curious, however, about attitudes toward U.S. Vietnamese among veterans and non-veterans alike. If Vietnam is a bad memory, what are we?<br><br>
It seems that all talk about Vietnamese places us/them squarely in the past and at a &quot;safe&quot; distance, now. What do people feel about Kim Phuc --the Canadian Vietnamese woman who was the little girl in that (in)famous photo running naked into the street after being napalmed by a US-led attack-- what do people think about her speaking at the Vietnam Veterans Memorial Wall at the last Memorial Day Commemoration? The local newcast I saw was distinctly resentful, something about how at least she was alive.<br><br>
 
